cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with specifying rules for acceptable behavior in a shared environment using a learning system that interacts with users to find an optimal solution. This involves active preference learning, Bayesian learning models, and simulations in realistic industrial environments. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
